Q.2. Prime Number Check

> Description;

--Problem Statement:
Given a number N, check whether it is prime or not. Print 'yes' if it is prime else print 'no'.


--Input Description:
The input consists of a single integer N.


--Output Description:
The output is 'yes' if N is prime, otherwise 'no'.


--Sample Input:
123


--Sample Output:
no

=> Code Solution :
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in);
        
        
        int N = input.nextInt();
        
        if (N <= 1) {
            System.out.println("no");
            return; 
        }

        boolean isPrime = true; // Use a flag to track if it's prime
        
        for (int i = 2; i <= (int) Math.sqrt(N); i++) {
            if (N % i == 0) {
                isPrime = false; // It found a factor!
                break;           // Exit the loop immediately
            }
        }

        if (isPrime) {
            System.out.println("yes");
        } else {
            System.out.println("no");
        }
        
        input.close();
    }
}

Output :
Correct 
case 1 
case 2
